444
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:17,919
Dogmatic, now since the Enlightenment, dogmatic has come to mean a bad thing.

445
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:23,520
You ought to be able to give good arguments for everything and not just go around and say that's how it is.

446
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:31,760
When Kierkegaard says dogmatic, he means he knows it by way of the revelation that's in the Bible, and there's no other way to know it.

447
00:42:31,759 --> 00:42:33,599
There's no rational way to know it.

448
00:42:33,599 --> 00:42:35,840
You can't prove it with biology.

449
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:42,960
You can't prove it by arguments like metaphysicians try to do and so forth.

450
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:46,160
You either got the revelation or you.

451
00:42:46,159 --> 00:42:48,799
In a certain way, you could say either you believe it or you don't.

452
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:55,039
