625
00:58:27,079 --> 00:58:30,279
And I keep wanting to say to him, suffering isn't what it's all about.

626
00:58:30,280 --> 00:58:31,720
It's about meaning.

627
00:58:31,719 --> 00:58:35,639
And the unconditional commitment is getting meaning in your life.

628
00:58:35,639 --> 00:58:39,879
And it gets tied up with a great deal of possible grief and suffering and so forth.

629
00:58:39,880 --> 00:58:42,840
But it's worth suffering to get meaning.

630
00:58:42,840 --> 00:58:48,760
And he says, no, no, there's only one really important thing in the world, and that is you shouldn't suffer.

631
00:58:48,759 --> 00:58:50,759
And that, and so.

632
00:58:50,759 --> 00:58:51,959
And what do you say to that?

633
00:58:51,960 --> 00:58:59,879
Well, you say you, what view you have about that will depend on what language you've grown up in and what tradition and what sort of family and so forth.

634
00:58:59,880 --> 00:59:00,359
Yeah.

635
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:05,319
What about the culture?

636
00:59:08,360 --> 00:59:09,799
Oh, oh, well, the atheist.

637
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:22,039
Ah, you're just, she's asking about what are the people who, what about the people who want to break out of this whole bliss addiction and this unconditional commitment story?

638
00:59:22,039 --> 00:59:23,799
Well, you're getting ahead of the story.

639
00:59:24,119 --> 00:59:25,639
And they are atheists.

640
00:59:25,639 --> 00:59:27,160
And they are nihilists.

641
00:59:27,159 --> 00:59:36,039
