642
00:59:36,039 --> 00:59:38,360
And guess who their leader is?

643
00:59:38,679 --> 00:59:39,800
Nietzsche.

644
00:59:39,800 --> 00:59:41,119
And we will get to Nietzsche.

645
00:59:40,280 --> 00:59:45,199
Nietzsche wants to break out of this, but he hates Buddhism as much as he hates Christianity.

646
00:59:45,679 --> 01:00:01,360
He's got his own new religion, which a lot of us are in now, because this we're kind of transitioned between the culture, which was a religious culture, and a secular kind of culture.

647
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:05,680
And so, your question is fine, and of course, we will get there.

648
01:00:06,559 --> 01:00:07,760
Anything else?

649
01:00:07,759 --> 01:00:08,400
Yeah.

650
01:00:10,960 --> 01:00:11,839
Logic?

651
01:00:12,159 --> 01:00:12,720
No.

652
01:00:13,039 --> 01:00:14,320
I certainly don't.

653
01:00:14,320 --> 01:00:15,039
It's funny.

654
01:00:15,039 --> 01:00:17,759
In fact, it's so, but you can't appreciate this.

655
01:00:17,759 --> 01:00:26,320
My son gives me these 4,000-year-old Buddhist arguments about space and time and how they're unreal and the objects are empty.

656
01:00:26,320 --> 01:00:29,520
And it sounds exactly like Kant's critique of pure reason.

657
01:00:29,520 --> 01:00:33,840
I mean, you can get to this, apparently, by logic and rationality.

658
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:39,120
You can get to Buddhism, or you can get to what Kant calls transcendental idealism.

659
01:00:39,119 --> 01:00:41,520
And it looks very similar.

660
01:00:41,679 --> 01:00:43,120
It's amazing.

661
01:00:43,119 --> 01:00:47,839
I think, this is just totally crazy, probably, but it's certainly striking.

662
01:00:47,840 --> 01:00:51,679
It looks to me like it's no accident that a philosophy.

663
01:00:52,239 --> 01:01:16,639
Either there's some really sort of innate way the mind works, and logic and rationality just come out the same, whether you're doing it in Tibet or in Knigsberg, Germany, or I think, in my opinion, having talked to my son and learned a lot from him, that we got this Buddhist thing straight out of Buddhism.

664
01:01:16,639 --> 01:01:24,879
Plato went away for a while, and Plato came to visit people who had something which people would talk about, the mystery religions.

665
01:01:24,880 --> 01:01:26,759
I don't know much about this, but I know this.

666
01:01:27,079 --> 01:01:33,320
Plato came back believing in the reincarnation of souls, and he didn't believe it when he left.

667
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:35,880
And it's a totally basic Buddhist idea.

668
01:01:35,880 --> 01:01:39,079
And he came back believing in karma, though he didn't call it karma.

669
01:01:39,079 --> 01:01:55,640
He said that the souls, before they got re-put in a body, which was a bad thing for them, but it had to be done, before they got re-put in a body, the past life they had determined what life they chose for their next life.

670
01:01:55,800 --> 01:01:58,599
See, if you know Buddhism, that sounds very familiar.

671
01:01:58,599 --> 01:02:06,520
What they did and thought and so forth in one life is going to determine whether they get a better life next round or a worse life next round.

672
01:02:06,520 --> 01:02:07,799
Plato got that.

673
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:09,800
Where did he get that all of a sudden?

674
01:02:09,800 --> 01:02:11,480
I think he got it from the Buddhist.

675
01:02:11,480 --> 01:02:15,639
And then you get all sorts of further things, which I won't go into with it.

676
01:02:15,639 --> 01:02:21,559
Plato's got once you believe that there's this other world.

677
01:02:21,559 --> 01:02:30,679
And he certainly thinks that getting stuck with the body is a kind of suffering, and you should die to the body as much as possible, and so forth.

678
01:02:30,679 --> 01:02:40,199
So it may not be an accident that if you do philosophy, lots of the arguments that come up look like they come from the Buddhist.

679
01:02:40,520 --> 01:02:41,559
I don't know.

680
01:02:41,559 --> 01:02:42,200
Yeah.

681
01:02:46,679 --> 01:02:48,520
Aha, very good question.

682
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:50,440
Is my son the Buddhist going to play with?

683
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:53,719
The answer is yes and no.

